    "body": "This new `AvroDataFileReader ` is introduced in PR https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/pull/5421, and can get better perf for cloud reading.\r\nWe may want to apply it to Avro PERFILE reading, but perf will become a little worse when reading local files.\r\n```\r\nLocal\uff1a\r\n      Files     CPU        PERFILE-new   PERFILE-old\r\n      400       25.023     10.172        9.582 \r\n      1000      27.141     16.441        12.722 \r\n      2000      27.179     26.146        21.882 \r\n\r\nCloud\uff1a                                     \r\n      128GB     94.134     88.834        830.753 \r\n      1GB       402.612    341.626       3632.736\r\n```\r\nSo shall we do this ? And what's the typical case for PERFILE reading, local or cloud ?",
